      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a weird loud humming sound but the fan isnt actually spinning. its just sitting there vibrating and humming. what could be causing that and is it safe for me to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming sound with no fan spin on your AC unit could be a few things, like a seized motor or a capacitor issue. It's best to be cautious, as electrical components can be dangerous, so unless you're a seasoned technician, it's safer to call a professional. A qualified HVAC repair person can diagnose the problem safely and get your unit running again.",
